<h3>Life expectancy has improved globally</h3>
Life expectancy in each region of the world stayed fairly stable for most of history until the onset of the ‚Äúhealth transition,‚Äù the period in which life expectancy began to increase. The chart below shows that the health transition began at different times in different regions; Oceania began to see increases in life expectancy around 1870, while Africa didn‚Äôt begin to see increases until around 1920.
<iframe style="width: 100%; height: 600px; border: 0px none;" src="https://ourworldindata.org/grapher/life-expectancy-globally-since-1770" width="300" height="150"></iframe>
